metatags.og:description: The Minnesota Digital Library has created a two-part timeline on Minnesota history featuring materials from our digital collections. These timelines explore significant moments in the history and development of the state. We encourage you to learn how local history connects with major world events in these timelines.

metatags.twitter:title: Borrow scanning equipment with MDL's Scan for Keeps program
metatags.og:title: Borrow scanning equipment with MDL's Scan for Keeps program
metatags.og:description: The Scan for Keeps program was developed to provide equipment for community scanning events and digitization projects around the state. Kits are available for libraries, historical societies, and other organizations to encourage community engagement and foster preservation education.
